Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
setLatencyFile(25.10)                                    setLatencyFile(25.10)

Name
       setLatencyFile - Specifies the latency file that the timing engine must
       load when the timing analysis mode is set to -usefulSkew

Syntax
       setLatencyFile

       [-help]

       <latencyFileName>

       Specifies  the  latency  file that the timing engine must load when the
       timing analysis mode is set to -usefulSkew.

       To see the current settings for the setLatencyFile command, see  getLa-
       tencyFile.

Parameters
       -help  Outputs  a  brief description that includes type and default in-
              formation for each setLatencyFile parameter. For a detailed  de-
              scription  of the command and all of its parameters, use the man
              command:

              man setLatencyFile

       <latencyFileName>
              Specifies the latency file to load.

Command Order
       Use this command after setting analysis mode to -usefulSkew.  For  more
       information, see the Timing Analysis chapter in the Innovus User Guide.

Example
       The following example sets the latency filename to latency1.

       setLatencyFile latency1

